Package org.apache.logging.log4j.async.logger

Class RingBufferLogEvent

java.lang.Object
org.apache.logging.log4j.async.logger.RingBufferLogEvent
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, CharSequence, LogEvent, ReusableLogEvent, org.apache.logging.log4j.message.Message, org.apache.logging.log4j.message.ParameterVisitable, org.apache.logging.log4j.message.ReusableMessage, org.apache.logging.log4j.util.StringBuilderFormattable
public class RingBufferLogEvent extends Object implements ReusableLogEvent, org.apache.logging.log4j.message.ReusableMessage, CharSequence, org.apache.logging.log4j.message.ParameterVisitable
When the Disruptor is started, the RingBuffer is populated with event objects. These objects are then re-used during the life of the RingBuffer.
